Researchers have found that bird species are continuing to drop in Fukushima after the disaster in 2011 . 
  The barn swallow, for example, dropped from hundreds to dozens . 
  This is despite radiation levels in the region starting to fall . 
  Scientists analysed 57 species and found that the majority of populations had diminished as a result of the nuclear accident . 
  And comparing it to Chernobyl could reveal what the future holds  . 
  The research was carried out by scientists at the University of South Carolina . 
 